entry.title: Chile's Presidential Election Pits Young Versus Old in Key Vote for Economy
entry.content: Voters in Latin America’s most affluent country are casting ballots following a campaign that has highlighted a generational divide pitting the young, who support presidential candidate Gabriel Boric, against the old, who are backing José Antonio Kast.

entry.title: The WorldWantsGreen Hydrogen. NamibiaSays It Can Deliver.
entry.content: The southern African nation of sun-laden deserts and wind-swept coastline is aiming to develop a hydrogen industry from renewable sources to meet growing global demand.
